{"build_type":"executable","module_name":"thread-execution-writes-shared-marker-global","package_name":"thread-execution-writes-shared-marker-global","description":"Thread body run by a spawned thread (the entry of a spawn_thread_running_entry). Writes a distinctive sentinel into the shared global g_thread_marker (visible to the parent because CLONE_VM shares the address space) then returns; the spawn render then thread-exits the child. Proof that the spawned thread really ran on its own stack.","module_globals":[{"global_name":"g_thread_marker","global_type":"i64","global_init":"0"}],"function_definitions":{"thread-execution-writes-shared-marker-global":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"sentinel","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":51966},{"instruction_type":"global_write","name":"g_thread_marker","value":"sentinel"},{"instruction_type":"return_statement","return_payload":{"value":"zero"}}]}}}